(1636, 0, 'Great Old One Patron', 'trait', NULL, 'classes', '{\"tag\": \"trait0\", \"name\": \"Great Old One Patron\", \"type\": \"trait\", \"levelMin\": \"1\", \"priority\": \"1\", \"description\": \"[Name] draws corrupting magic and other unspeakable secrets from the being known as [patron]. This entity is as ancient as reality itself and its motives are incomprehensible to the mortals of this world. It might be unaware of [name]\'s existence or totally indifferent to [them], but [name] feels its influence tainting [their] mind each time [they] draws power from it.\"}'),
(1637, 0, 'Create Thrall', 'legendary', NULL, 'classes', '{\"tag\": \"legendary0\", \"cost\": \"2\", \"name\": \"Create Thrall\", \"type\": \"legendary\", \"ability\": \"STR\", \"levelMin\": \"17\", \"priority\": \"20\", \"description\": \"[Name] infects a humanoid\'s mind with the alien magic of [patron]. [Name] touches an incapacitated humanoid within reach. That creature is then charmed by [name] until a [spell:Remove Curse] spell is cast on it, the charmed condition is removed from it, or [name] uses this feature again. [Name] can communicate telepathically with the charmed creature as long as both of them are in the same plane of existence.\"}'),
(1638, 0, 'Book of Shadows', 'trait', NULL, 'classes', '{\"tag\": \"trait4\", \"name\": \"Book of Shadows\", \"type\": \"trait\", \"levelMin\": \"9\", \"priority\": \"20\", \"description\": \"[Name] has found a old grimoire written in a lost language. This book contains encrypted knowledge passed from [patron] to those who came before [name], and [they] is desperately trying to decipher it. By studying this book [name] has so far acquired these powers:\\n- [Name] no longer needs to sleep and can\'t be forced to sleep by any means.\\n- [Name] can cast [their] 1st level spells as rituals without expending spell slots.\\n- If a creature writes its name on a specific page of the book, [name] can write in the same page a message to that creature at any time. The creature hears the message in its mind and, if it replies, its message appears on the page. The writing disappears after 1 minute.\\n- If a creature writes its name on a specific page of the book, it can be protected from death after being injured. When the creature is reduced to 0 hit points but not killed outright, the creature magically drops to 1 hit point instead. Once this magic is triggered, no creature can benefit from it until [name] finishes a long rest.\\n- If [name] loses the book, [they] can perform a 1-hour ceremony to summon it.\\n\"}'),
